:::.row
:::.col-12 .col-md-6
Igneous rocks are rocks formed by the `cooling and solidification` of molten material known as `magma` (inside Earth) or `lava` (on Earth’s surface). They represent the primary rocks of Earth’s crust and serve as the `origin for sedimentary and metamorphic rocks`.
